&lt;p&gt;We believe life insurance innovation must happen in the context of sound underwriting decisions. The Director, Underwriting will lead Ladder’s underwriting team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage 3 UW teams and develop their skill sets in line with our underwriting philosophy and guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Production UW&amp;nbsp; (Analyze medical, non-medical, and financial data to accept, modify, or decline risks on applications referred to manual underwriting)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Auditing UW (both requirements from our carriers - and also small special audits we need to run to improve the product)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Projects UW (subject matter experts providing input into any changes to our digital instant UW to improve the business while being wise on the risk)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain relationships and stay on the cutting edge of new third party data offerings. Identify, pilot, and engage new tools to improve underwriting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with our insurance partners in concert with Ladder’s business development director who leads the relationship management of our reinsurers and carriers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with actuary to present mortality slippage each month to Ladder’s mortality team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a subject matter expert to engineering and product teams as we build new insurance offerings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
